                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">871.6363/231: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-09T19:00:00+01:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1924—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 9—6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Department’s 42, October 7, 4 p.m. Today I communicated orally to Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs substance of telegram under reference. He said he would take
                    matter up with Minister of Industry and Commerce and he believed a solution
                    would be reached satisfactory to the American Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Riggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
